v47 is built on top of v43. Entry logic is unchanged — only the exit logic is different.

Entry (unchanged from v37/v43)
Every 1-minute bar, scan for:

ATM OI imbalance ≥ 15% (puts significantly outweigh calls → bullish, or vice versa)
Outer OI (ATM±1,±2) imbalance ≥ 6%, same direction
ATM ratio ≥ 1.5× (one side at least 1.5× the other)
OI trend consistent for last 3 minutes
CALL entries blocked if spot is flat (within -30 to 0 pts of open) — avoids chop
Entry at ATM+2 strike for CALL, ATM-2 strike for PUT (buy far OTM option premium)
Exit — The v47 Hybrid
This is what makes v47 different. After entry, the trade goes through two phases based on time elapsed:

Phase 1: First 5 bars (bars 0–5 minutes) — "Fast-Fail Gate"
Uses v37-style ATM-alone exit:

Each bar: check ATM OI direction and imbalance
If ATM signal fails (imbalance < 7% OR direction flipped against us): increment oi_exit_consec
If ATM signal holds: reset counter to 0
If oi_exit_consec >= 2 (fails 2 bars in a row): exit immediately → reason = OI_EXIT_EARLY_ATM
Why this phase exists: When you enter at ATM+2 (far OTM), if the ATM signal fades within the first 5 minutes, it means the momentum that triggered entry is already dying. The market hasn't committed to your direction. Cut early with a small profit or near-breakeven instead of holding until an 18% SL.

These were the "dead trades" in v43 — 29 trades that stayed FAR_OTM all the way to SL. In v47, 27 of them are caught here at 100% win rate, avg +₹748.

Phase 2: After 5 bars — "Dynamic Zone Exit" (v43 logic)
If the trade survives the first 5 bars (ATM signal held), it means the momentum is real. Now the exit adapts to where the entry strike is currently sitting relative to the live ATM:

Entry strike current position → Zone → What OI to watch → Trigger
─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
CALL offset ≥ +2  (still far OTM)  → FAR_OTM   → ATM + outer(±1,±2)  → BOTH fail × 2 bars
CALL offset = +1  (one step closer) → NEAR_OTM  → ATM + ring(±1 only) → BOTH fail × 2 bars
CALL offset =  0  (reached ATM)    → ATM        → ATM only             → single fail × 2 bars
CALL offset ≤ -1  (gone ITM!)      → ITM        → ATM reversal watch   → immediate exit, no wait
(PUT is the mirror: offset ≤ -2 = FAR_OTM, offset = -1 = NEAR_OTM, etc.)

The key insight: As the underlying moves in your direction, the entry strike drifts closer to ATM. The monitoring tightens — fewer OI signals need to fail to trigger an exit, because at ATM and ITM you're already in profit and the risk profile changes.

FAR_OTM: patient — both ATM AND outer signals must fail. One signal can fluctuate without exiting.
NEAR_OTM: both ATM AND the immediate ring must fail. Outer (±2) no longer relevant.
ATM: just ATM alone failing twice is enough — you're at-the-money, time to lock in.
ITM: exit immediately the moment ATM OI flips against you — no waiting. Strike has gone in the money; a reversal here is a real threat.
Premium Exits (all versions, checked first every bar)
Before OI logic runs, each bar checks premium directly:

Condition	Action
Premium drops 18% from entry	SL_HIT — hard stop
Premium doubles (+100%)	TARGET_HIT — full target
Premium rises 70% → trail armed	Trail mode ON
Trail armed + premium falls back to +20%	TRAIL_SL — locked trail
SL fires before OI exit on the same bar.

Hard Exit
At 15:19 IST, any open trade is closed at market regardless of OI signal. This is a hard market-hours cutoff.

Why v47 Beats v43
Scenario	v43 outcome	v47 outcome
Entry signal fades in first 5 min	Holds patiently waiting for both-fail → often runs to SL	Caught in 5 bars → exits at small profit/flat
Signal holds 5+ bars, strike drifts to ATM	Dynamic zone exits at right time → big win	Same — dynamic zone kicks in
Strike stays FAR_OTM but signal is real	Holds correctly → exits when both signals fail	Holds correctly — same as v43
The 5-bar early gate cuts the dead trades without touching the good ones. That's why P&L is nearly identical to v43 (₹69.5k vs ₹70.6k) but win rate jumped 4.5pp and PF improved from 3.73 → 4.13.




"""
OI Divergence Strategy  v47  -- Dynamic Zone Exit + Hybrid Early ATM Check
===========================================================================
Base: v43

ADDED: Hybrid early ATM check
  For the first EARLY_ATM_BARS minutes after entry (while still in FAR_OTM):
    use v37-style ATM-alone exit (single ATM signal fail x EXIT_PERSIST bars)
  After EARLY_ATM_BARS: switch to v43's both-fail dynamic zone logic

  Rationale: if ATM signal fades in the first 5 minutes, the entry was marginal.
  Cut early like v37. If ATM holds for 5+ bars, the signal is real -- hold with
  v43's more patient logic to capture bigger moves.
  EARLY_ATM_BARS = 5 minutes.

Run: py backtest_v47.py
"""

import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
from pathlib import Path

DATA_FILE  = Path(__file__).parent / "atm_joined_2026.parquet"
OUT_DIR    = Path(__file__).parent / "results"
OUT_DIR.mkdir(exist_ok=True)

LAKH = 100_000
LOT  = 75

ATM_IMBALANCE_MIN   = 0.15
OUTER_IMBALANCE_MIN = 0.06
EXIT_IMBALANCE_MIN  = 0.07

OI_TREND_MINS        = 3
MIN_ATM_RATIO        = 1.5
MAX_OUTER_ATM_RATIO  = 5.0
MAX_ENTRY_PREMIUM    = 180.0
EXIT_PERSIST         = 2
EARLY_ATM_BARS       = 5   # first N bars: v37-style ATM-alone exit, then v43 dynamic zone
MAX_TRADES_DAY       = 4

SL_PCT         = 0.18
TARGET_PCT     = 1.00
TRAIL_TRIG_PCT = 0.70
TRAIL_LOCK_PCT = 0.20

SCAN_START       = pd.Timestamp("09:20").time()
ENTRY_CUTOFF     = pd.Timestamp("15:15").time()
HARD_EXIT        = pd.Timestamp("15:19").time()
MIN_PREMIUM      = 30.0
REENTRY_COOLDOWN = 5
DAILY_LOSS_LIMIT = -8000
BLOCK_HOUR_START = pd.Timestamp("10:00").time()
BLOCK_HOUR_END   = pd.Timestamp("10:59").time()

CALL_BLOCK_ZONE_LOW  = -30.0
CALL_BLOCK_ZONE_HIGH =   0.0


def load_data():
    df = pd.read_parquet(DATA_FILE)
    df["timestamp"] = pd.to_datetime(df["timestamp"])
    df["date"] = df["timestamp"].dt.date
    df.sort_values(["timestamp", "strike_offset"], inplace=True)
    return df


def atm_oi(snap):
    row = snap[snap["strike_offset"] == 0]
    if row.empty:
        return 0, 0
    return int(row.iloc[0]["oi_call"]), int(row.iloc[0]["oi_put"])


def outer_oi(snap):
    c = snap[snap["strike_offset"].isin([1, 2])]["oi_call"].sum()
    p = snap[snap["strike_offset"].isin([-1, -2])]["oi_put"].sum()
    return int(c), int(p)


def imbalance_ratio(a, b):
    total = a + b
    if total == 0:
        return 0.0
    return abs(a - b) / total


def atm_ratio_val(atm_c, atm_p):
    if atm_c == 0 or atm_p == 0:
        return 0.0
    return max(atm_p / atm_c, atm_c / atm_p)


def check_oi_direction(snap):
    atm_c, atm_p     = atm_oi(snap)
    outer_c, outer_p = outer_oi(snap)
    atm_imb   = imbalance_ratio(atm_c, atm_p)
    outer_imb = imbalance_ratio(outer_c, outer_p)
    atm_dir   = "CALL" if atm_c < atm_p else "PUT"
    outer_dir = "CALL" if outer_c < outer_p else "PUT"
    return atm_dir, outer_dir, atm_imb, outer_imb, atm_c, atm_p, outer_c, outer_p


def oi_trend_ok(day_df, current_ts, signal_dir, lookback):
    atm_rows = day_df[day_df["strike_offset"] == 0].sort_values("timestamp")
    past = atm_rows[atm_rows["timestamp"] <= current_ts].tail(lookback)
    if len(past) < lookback:
        return False
    for _, row in past.iterrows():
        c = int(row["oi_call"]); p = int(row["oi_put"])
        if ("CALL" if c < p else "PUT") != signal_dir:
            return False
    return True


def get_entry_strike_zone(snap, entry_strike, direction):
    """
    Find how far the entry_strike has moved relative to the CURRENT ATM.
    Returns (current_offset, zone).

    CALL zones:  offset>=2 -> FAR_OTM  | +1 -> NEAR_OTM | 0 -> ATM | <0 -> ITM
    PUT zones:   offset<=-2 -> FAR_OTM | -1 -> NEAR_OTM | 0 -> ATM | >0 -> ITM
    """
    row = snap[snap["strike"] == entry_strike]
    if row.empty:
        return 2, "FAR_OTM"   # default: treat as still far OTM if data missing
    current_offset = int(row.iloc[0]["strike_offset"])

    if direction == "CALL":
        if current_offset >= 2:    zone = "FAR_OTM"
        elif current_offset == 1:  zone = "NEAR_OTM"
        elif current_offset == 0:  zone = "ATM"
        else:                      zone = "ITM"        # offset <= -1
    else:   # PUT
        if current_offset <= -2:   zone = "FAR_OTM"
        elif current_offset == -1: zone = "NEAR_OTM"
        elif current_offset == 0:  zone = "ATM"
        else:                      zone = "ITM"        # offset >= +1

    return current_offset, zone


def dynamic_oi_exit(snap, entry_strike, direction):
    """
    Zone-aware OI exit decision.

    Returns:
      both_failed    (bool) -- increment oi_exit_consec counter (persist still required)
      immediate_exit (bool) -- skip counter, exit NOW (ITM reversal)
      zone           (str)  -- current zone label for the trade record
      current_offset (int)
    """
    current_offset, zone = get_entry_strike_zone(snap, entry_strike, direction)

    atm_c, atm_p = atm_oi(snap)
    atm_imb   = imbalance_ratio(atm_c, atm_p)
    atm_dir   = "CALL" if atm_c < atm_p else "PUT"
    atm_ok    = (atm_imb >= EXIT_IMBALANCE_MIN) and (atm_dir == direction)

    if zone == "FAR_OTM":
        # v42 behavior: ATM + outer (+-1,+-2), both must fail
        outer_c, outer_p = outer_oi(snap)
        outer_imb = imbalance_ratio(outer_c, outer_p)
        outer_dir = "CALL" if outer_c < outer_p else "PUT"
        outer_ok  = (outer_imb >= EXIT_IMBALANCE_MIN) and (outer_dir == direction)
        both_failed = (not atm_ok) and (not outer_ok)
        return both_failed, False, zone, current_offset

    elif zone == "NEAR_OTM":
        # Reduced ring: ATM + (ATM+1 call vs ATM-1 put), both must fail
        ring_c = int(snap[snap["strike_offset"] == 1]["oi_call"].sum())
        ring_p = int(snap[snap["strike_offset"] == -1]["oi_put"].sum())
        ring_imb = imbalance_ratio(ring_c, ring_p)
        ring_dir = "CALL" if ring_c < ring_p else "PUT"
        ring_ok  = (ring_imb >= EXIT_IMBALANCE_MIN) and (ring_dir == direction)
        both_failed = (not atm_ok) and (not ring_ok)
        return both_failed, False, zone, current_offset

    elif zone == "ATM":
        # Only ATM OI -- single fail is enough (persist still applies)
        return (not atm_ok), False, zone, current_offset

    else:   # ITM
        # Reversal watch: if ATM OI has flipped against our direction -> exit NOW
        reversal = (atm_dir != direction)
        return False, reversal, zone, current_offset


def check_premium_exit(entry_px, current_px, trail_on):
    if current_px <= entry_px * (1 - SL_PCT):
        return True, "SL_HIT", trail_on
    if current_px >= entry_px * (1 + TARGET_PCT):
        return True, "TARGET_HIT", trail_on
    if current_px >= entry_px * (1 + TRAIL_TRIG_PCT):
        trail_on = True
    if trail_on and current_px <= entry_px * (1 + TRAIL_LOCK_PCT):
        return True, "TRAIL_SL", trail_on
    return False, None, trail_on


OFFSET_LABEL = {2: "ATM+2", 1: "ATM+1", 0: "ATM", -1: "ATM-1", -2: "ATM-2"}


def make_record(date, entry_ts, exit_ts, direction, entry_strike,
                entry_px, exit_px, pnl, reason, trade_num,
                atm_c, atm_p, outer_c, outer_p,
                atm_imb, outer_imb,
                open_ref, entry_spot, entry_offset,
                exit_zone=None, exit_strike_offset=None,
                exit_snap=None):
    def _L(v): return round(v / LAKH, 1) if v is not None else None
    def _pct(v): return round(v * 100, 1) if v is not None else None

    ex_atm_c = ex_atm_p = ex_outer_c = ex_outer_p = ex_atm_strike = None
    ex_atm_imb = ex_outer_imb = None
    if exit_snap is not None and not exit_snap.empty:
        arow = exit_snap[exit_snap["strike_offset"] == 0]
        if not arow.empty:
            ex_atm_strike = float(arow.iloc[0]["strike"])
            ex_atm_c = int(arow.iloc[0]["oi_call"])
            ex_atm_p = int(arow.iloc[0]["oi_put"])
            ex_atm_imb = imbalance_ratio(ex_atm_c, ex_atm_p)
        oc = exit_snap[exit_snap["strike_offset"].isin([1, 2])]["oi_call"].sum()
        op = exit_snap[exit_snap["strike_offset"].isin([-1, -2])]["oi_put"].sum()
        ex_outer_c = int(oc); ex_outer_p = int(op)
        ex_outer_imb = imbalance_ratio(ex_outer_c, ex_outer_p)

    return {
        "date":                  date,
        "day":                   pd.Timestamp(str(date)).day_name()[:3],
        "trade_num":             trade_num,
        "entry_time":            entry_ts.strftime("%H:%M"),
        "exit_time":             exit_ts.strftime("%H:%M") if exit_ts else None,
        "direction":             direction,
        "entry_strike":          entry_strike,
        "entry_offset":          OFFSET_LABEL.get(entry_offset, str(entry_offset)),
        "exit_zone":             exit_zone,
        "exit_strike_offset":    exit_strike_offset,
        "entry_atm_call_L":      _L(atm_c),
        "entry_atm_put_L":       _L(atm_p),
        "entry_atm_diff_L":      _L(abs(atm_c - atm_p)),
        "entry_atm_imb_pct":     _pct(atm_imb),
        "entry_outer_call_L":    _L(outer_c),
        "entry_outer_put_L":     _L(outer_p),
        "entry_outer_diff_L":    _L(abs(outer_c - outer_p)),
        "entry_outer_imb_pct":   _pct(outer_imb),
        "atm_ratio":             round(atm_ratio_val(atm_c, atm_p), 2),
        "open_ref":              round(open_ref, 1) if open_ref else None,
        "entry_spot":            round(entry_spot, 1),
        "spot_vs_open":          round(entry_spot - open_ref, 1) if open_ref else None,
        "entry_premium":         round(entry_px, 2),
        "exit_premium":          round(exit_px, 2),
        "pnl_per_lot":           round(pnl, 2),
        "exit_reason":           reason,
        "duration_min":          int((exit_ts - entry_ts).seconds / 60) if exit_ts else None,
        "exit_atm_strike":       ex_atm_strike,
        "exit_atm_call_L":       _L(ex_atm_c),
        "exit_atm_put_L":        _L(ex_atm_p),
        "exit_atm_diff_L":       _L(abs(ex_atm_c - ex_atm_p)) if ex_atm_c is not None else None,
        "exit_atm_imb_pct":      _pct(ex_atm_imb),
        "exit_outer_call_L":     _L(ex_outer_c),
        "exit_outer_put_L":      _L(ex_outer_p),
        "exit_outer_diff_L":     _L(abs(ex_outer_c - ex_outer_p)) if ex_outer_c is not None else None,
        "exit_outer_imb_pct":    _pct(ex_outer_imb),
    }


def backtest_day(day_df, date):
    trades     = []
    timestamps = sorted(day_df["timestamp"].unique())

    def snap(ts):
        return day_df[day_df["timestamp"] == ts]

    ts_open   = pd.Timestamp(str(date) + " 09:15:00")
    open_snap = snap(ts_open)
    if open_snap.empty and timestamps:
        open_snap = day_df[day_df["timestamp"] == timestamps[0]]
    open_ref = float(open_snap.iloc[0]["spot"]) if not open_snap.empty else None

    in_trade       = False
    entry_px = entry_ts = direction = entry_strike = entry_offset = None
    e_atm_c = e_atm_p = e_outer_c = e_outer_p = e_spot = None
    e_atm_imb = e_outer_imb = None
    e_trade_num    = 0
    trail_on       = False
    oi_exit_consec = 0
    last_zone      = "FAR_OTM"

    day_pnl      = 0.0
    trades_today = 0
    reentry_after = None

    for ts in timestamps:
        t = ts.time()
        if t < SCAN_START:
            continue

        if t > HARD_EXIT:
            if in_trade:
                s   = snap(ts)
                row = s[s["strike"] == entry_strike]
                col = "close_call" if direction == "CALL" else "close_put"
                px  = float(row.iloc[0][col]) if not row.empty else entry_px
                pnl = (px - entry_px) * LOT
                day_pnl += pnl
                trades.append(make_record(
                    date, entry_ts, ts, direction, entry_strike,
                    entry_px, px, pnl, "HARD_EXIT", e_trade_num,
                    e_atm_c, e_atm_p, e_outer_c, e_outer_p,
                    e_atm_imb, e_outer_imb,
                    open_ref, e_spot, entry_offset,
                    exit_zone=last_zone, exit_snap=s))
                in_trade = False
            break

        s        = snap(ts)
        cur_spot = float(s.iloc[0]["spot"]) if not s.empty else np.nan

        if in_trade:
            row = s[s["strike"] == entry_strike]
            if row.empty:
                continue
            col        = "close_call" if direction == "CALL" else "close_put"
            current_px = float(row.iloc[0][col])
            if np.isnan(current_px):
                continue

            # Premium exits first (SL / target / trail -- unchanged)
            should_exit, reason, trail_on = check_premium_exit(
                entry_px, current_px, trail_on)
            if should_exit:
                pnl = (current_px - entry_px) * LOT
                day_pnl += pnl
                _, _, last_zone, cur_off = dynamic_oi_exit(s, entry_strike, direction)
                trades.append(make_record(
                    date, entry_ts, ts, direction, entry_strike,
                    entry_px, current_px, pnl, reason, e_trade_num,
                    e_atm_c, e_atm_p, e_outer_c, e_outer_p,
                    e_atm_imb, e_outer_imb,
                    open_ref, e_spot, entry_offset,
                    exit_zone=last_zone, exit_strike_offset=cur_off, exit_snap=s))
                in_trade       = False
                trail_on       = False
                oi_exit_consec = 0
                trades_today  += 1
                reentry_after  = ts + pd.Timedelta(minutes=REENTRY_COOLDOWN)
                continue

            # Hybrid OI exit
            bars_in_trade = int((ts - entry_ts).seconds / 60)

            if bars_in_trade <= EARLY_ATM_BARS:
                # Early phase (first EARLY_ATM_BARS mins): v37-style ATM-alone exit
                atm_c2, atm_p2 = atm_oi(s)
                atm_imb2 = imbalance_ratio(atm_c2, atm_p2)
                atm_dir2 = "CALL" if atm_c2 < atm_p2 else "PUT"
                atm_ok2  = (atm_imb2 >= EXIT_IMBALANCE_MIN) and (atm_dir2 == direction)
                if not atm_ok2:
                    oi_exit_consec += 1
                else:
                    oi_exit_consec = 0
                if oi_exit_consec >= EXIT_PERSIST:
                    pnl = (current_px - entry_px) * LOT
                    day_pnl += pnl
                    _, _, early_zone, early_off = dynamic_oi_exit(s, entry_strike, direction)
                    last_zone = early_zone
                    trades.append(make_record(
                        date, entry_ts, ts, direction, entry_strike,
                        entry_px, current_px, pnl, "OI_EXIT_EARLY_ATM", e_trade_num,
                        e_atm_c, e_atm_p, e_outer_c, e_outer_p,
                        e_atm_imb, e_outer_imb,
                        open_ref, e_spot, entry_offset,
                        exit_zone=early_zone, exit_strike_offset=early_off, exit_snap=s))
                    in_trade       = False
                    trail_on       = False
                    oi_exit_consec = 0
                    trades_today  += 1
                    reentry_after  = ts + pd.Timedelta(minutes=REENTRY_COOLDOWN)

            else:
                # Late phase (after EARLY_ATM_BARS): v43 dynamic zone logic
                both_failed, immediate_exit, zone, cur_off = dynamic_oi_exit(
                    s, entry_strike, direction)
                last_zone = zone

                if immediate_exit:
                    # ITM reversal -- exit NOW, no persist needed
                    pnl = (current_px - entry_px) * LOT
                    day_pnl += pnl
                    trades.append(make_record(
                        date, entry_ts, ts, direction, entry_strike,
                        entry_px, current_px, pnl, "OI_EXIT_ITM_REVERSAL", e_trade_num,
                        e_atm_c, e_atm_p, e_outer_c, e_outer_p,
                        e_atm_imb, e_outer_imb,
                        open_ref, e_spot, entry_offset,
                        exit_zone=zone, exit_strike_offset=cur_off, exit_snap=s))
                    in_trade       = False
                    trail_on       = False
                    oi_exit_consec = 0
                    trades_today  += 1
                    reentry_after  = ts + pd.Timedelta(minutes=REENTRY_COOLDOWN)

                elif both_failed:
                    oi_exit_consec += 1
                    if oi_exit_consec >= EXIT_PERSIST:
                        pnl = (current_px - entry_px) * LOT
                        day_pnl += pnl
                        reason_str = f"OI_EXIT_{zone}"
                        trades.append(make_record(
                            date, entry_ts, ts, direction, entry_strike,
                            entry_px, current_px, pnl, reason_str, e_trade_num,
                            e_atm_c, e_atm_p, e_outer_c, e_outer_p,
                            e_atm_imb, e_outer_imb,
                            open_ref, e_spot, entry_offset,
                            exit_zone=zone, exit_strike_offset=cur_off, exit_snap=s))
                        in_trade       = False
                        trail_on       = False
                        oi_exit_consec = 0
                        trades_today  += 1
                        reentry_after  = ts + pd.Timedelta(minutes=REENTRY_COOLDOWN)
                else:
                    oi_exit_consec = 0

        else:
            if t > ENTRY_CUTOFF:
                continue
            if trades_today >= MAX_TRADES_DAY:
                continue
            if day_pnl <= DAILY_LOSS_LIMIT:
                continue
            if reentry_after and ts < reentry_after:
                continue
            if BLOCK_HOUR_START <= t <= BLOCK_HOUR_END:
                continue

            atm_dir, outer_dir, atm_imb, outer_imb, atm_c, atm_p, outer_c, outer_p = \
                check_oi_direction(s)

            if atm_imb < ATM_IMBALANCE_MIN:
                continue
            if outer_imb < OUTER_IMBALANCE_MIN:
                continue
            if atm_dir != outer_dir:
                continue

            ratio = atm_ratio_val(atm_c, atm_p)
            if ratio < MIN_ATM_RATIO:
                continue

            atm_diff_now   = abs(atm_c - atm_p)
            outer_diff_now = abs(outer_c - outer_p)
            if atm_diff_now > 0 and (outer_diff_now / atm_diff_now) > MAX_OUTER_ATM_RATIO:
                continue

            sig_dir = atm_dir

            if open_ref is not None and not np.isnan(cur_spot):
                svopen = cur_spot - open_ref
                if sig_dir == "CALL" and CALL_BLOCK_ZONE_LOW <= svopen <= CALL_BLOCK_ZONE_HIGH:
                    continue

            if not oi_trend_ok(day_df, ts, sig_dir, OI_TREND_MINS):
                continue

            off = 2 if sig_dir == "CALL" else -2
            row = s[s["strike_offset"] == off]
            if row.empty:
                continue
            col = "close_call" if sig_dir == "CALL" else "close_put"
            px  = float(row.iloc[0][col])
            if np.isnan(px) or px < MIN_PREMIUM or px > MAX_ENTRY_PREMIUM:
                continue

            entry_px       = px
            entry_ts       = ts
            direction      = sig_dir
            entry_strike   = float(row.iloc[0]["strike"])
            entry_offset   = off
            e_atm_c, e_atm_p     = atm_c, atm_p
            e_outer_c, e_outer_p = outer_c, outer_p
            e_atm_imb, e_outer_imb = atm_imb, outer_imb
            e_spot         = cur_spot
            e_trade_num    = trades_today + 1
            in_trade       = True
            trail_on       = False
            oi_exit_consec = 0
            last_zone      = "FAR_OTM"

    return trades


def run_backtest(df):
    all_trades = []
    dates = sorted(df["date"].unique())
    print(f"Running v47 on {len(dates)} days  (dynamic zone exit + hybrid early ATM check)")
    print(f"  Entry: ATM imb>={ATM_IMBALANCE_MIN*100:.0f}%  outer imb>={OUTER_IMBALANCE_MIN*100:.0f}%  "
          f"ratio>={MIN_ATM_RATIO}  trend={OI_TREND_MINS}m")
    print(f"  Exit zones: FAR_OTM(both-fail) -> NEAR_OTM(ring-fail) -> ATM(single-fail) -> ITM(immediate-reversal)")
    print(f"  SL {int(SL_PCT*100)}% | Target {int(TARGET_PCT*100)}% | Trail @+{int(TRAIL_TRIG_PCT*100)}%/lock+{int(TRAIL_LOCK_PCT*100)}%")
    print()

    for d in dates:
        day_df = df[df["date"] == d].copy()
        trades = backtest_day(day_df, d)
        day_pnl = sum(tr["pnl_per_lot"] for tr in trades)
        dow = pd.Timestamp(str(d)).day_name()[:3]
        flag = "  <<< NEGATIVE" if day_pnl < 0 else ""
        print(f"  {d} ({dow})  trades={len(trades):2d}  P&L=INR {day_pnl:>10,.0f}{flag}")
        all_trades.extend(trades)

    return pd.DataFrame(all_trades)


def print_summary(df, dates_count):
    if df.empty:
        print("No trades generated.")
        return None

    wins   = df[df["pnl_per_lot"] > 0]
    losses = df[df["pnl_per_lot"] <= 0]
    n   = len(df)
    gp  = wins["pnl_per_lot"].sum()
    gl  = abs(losses["pnl_per_lot"].sum())
    net = df["pnl_per_lot"].sum()
    wr  = len(wins) / n * 100
    pf  = gp / gl if gl > 0 else float("inf")
    aw  = wins["pnl_per_lot"].mean() if len(wins) else 0
    al  = losses["pnl_per_lot"].mean() if len(losses) else 0
    exp = (wr / 100) * aw + (1 - wr / 100) * al
    cum = df["pnl_per_lot"].cumsum()
    mdd = (cum - cum.cummax()).min()
    streak = max_streak = 0
    for v in df["pnl_per_lot"]:
        streak = streak + 1 if v <= 0 else 0
        max_streak = max(max_streak, streak)

    day_pnl  = df.groupby("date")["pnl_per_lot"].sum()
    pos_days = (day_pnl > 0).sum()
    neg_days = (day_pnl <= 0).sum()

    rows = [
        ("Total Trades",         n),
        ("Trading Days",         dates_count),
        ("Days with Trades",     len(day_pnl)),
        ("Positive Days",        int(pos_days)),
        ("Negative Days",        int(neg_days)),
        ("Win Rate %",           round(wr, 1)),
        ("Net P&L INR",          round(net, 0)),
        ("Gross Profit INR",     round(gp, 0)),
        ("Gross Loss INR",       round(gl, 0)),
        ("Profit Factor",        round(pf, 2)),
        ("Avg Win INR",          round(aw, 0)),
        ("Avg Loss INR",         round(al, 0)),
        ("Expectancy INR",       round(exp, 0)),
        ("Max Drawdown INR",     round(mdd, 0)),
        ("Max Consec Losses",    max_streak),
        ("Avg Duration (min)",   round(df["duration_min"].mean(), 1)),
        ("Avg Trades/Day",       round(n / dates_count, 2)),
    ]
    for r, cnt in df["exit_reason"].value_counts().items():
        pnl_r = df[df["exit_reason"] == r]["pnl_per_lot"]
        rows.append((f"Exit: {r} (n={cnt})",
                     f"net={pnl_r.sum():,.0f}  avg={pnl_r.mean():,.0f}  wr={( pnl_r>0).mean()*100:.0f}%"))

    smry = pd.DataFrame(rows, columns=["Metric", "Value"])
    print()
    print("=" * 72)
    print("BACKTEST SUMMARY - v47  (dynamic zone + hybrid early ATM check)")
    print("=" * 72)
    print(smry.to_string(index=False))

    print("\n--- By Direction ---")
    for d2, g in df.groupby("direction"):
        w2 = (g["pnl_per_lot"] > 0).sum() / len(g) * 100
        sl = (g["exit_reason"] == "SL_HIT").sum()
        print(f"  {d2:4}  trades={len(g):3d}  win={w2:.1f}%  "
              f"avg={g['pnl_per_lot'].mean():>8.0f}  total={g['pnl_per_lot'].sum():>10.0f}  SL={sl}")

    print("\n--- By Exit Reason ---")
    for er, g in df.groupby("exit_reason"):
        w2 = (g["pnl_per_lot"] > 0).sum() / len(g) * 100
        print(f"  {er:<32}  trades={len(g):3d}  win={w2:.1f}%  "
              f"avg={g['pnl_per_lot'].mean():>8.0f}  total={g['pnl_per_lot'].sum():>10.0f}")

    print("\n--- Exit zone breakdown ---")
    if "exit_zone" in df.columns:
        for zn, g in df.groupby("exit_zone"):
            w2 = (g["pnl_per_lot"] > 0).sum() / len(g) * 100
            print(f"  {zn:<12}  trades={len(g):3d}  win={w2:.1f}%  "
                  f"avg={g['pnl_per_lot'].mean():>8.0f}  total={g['pnl_per_lot'].sum():>10.0f}")

    print("\n--- How deep did entry strikes go (exit_strike_offset at exit) ---")
    if "exit_strike_offset" in df.columns:
        eso = df["exit_strike_offset"].value_counts().sort_index()
        for off, cnt in eso.items():
            g = df[df["exit_strike_offset"] == off]
            w2 = (g["pnl_per_lot"] > 0).mean() * 100
            print(f"  offset={off:>3}  trades={cnt:3d}  win={w2:.1f}%  "
                  f"avg={g['pnl_per_lot'].mean():>8.0f}  net={g['pnl_per_lot'].sum():>10.0f}")

    print("\n--- By Day of Week ---")
    df["dow"] = pd.to_datetime(df["date"]).dt.day_name()
    for day in ["Monday","Tuesday","Wednesday","Thursday","Friday"]:
        g = df[df["dow"] == day]
        if g.empty: continue
        w2 = (g["pnl_per_lot"] > 0).sum() / len(g) * 100
        sl = (g["exit_reason"] == "SL_HIT").sum()
        print(f"  {day:<12}  trades={len(g):3d}  win={w2:.1f}%  "
              f"avg={g['pnl_per_lot'].mean():>8.0f}  total={g['pnl_per_lot'].sum():>10.0f}  SL={sl}")

    print("\n--- Entry hour ---")
    df["entry_hour"] = df["entry_time"].apply(lambda x: x[:2])
    for hr, g in df.groupby("entry_hour"):
        w2 = (g["pnl_per_lot"] > 0).sum() / len(g) * 100
        sl = (g["exit_reason"] == "SL_HIT").sum()
        print(f"  {hr}:xx  trades={len(g):3d}  win={w2:.1f}%  "
              f"avg={g['pnl_per_lot'].mean():>8.0f}  SL={sl}")

    print("\n--- Day-wise P&L ---")
    dpnl = day_pnl.reset_index()
    dpnl.columns = ["Date", "Net_PNL"]
    dpnl["Day"] = pd.to_datetime(dpnl["Date"]).dt.day_name().str[:3]
    dpnl["Cumulative"] = dpnl["Net_PNL"].cumsum()
    dpnl["Flag"] = dpnl["Net_PNL"].apply(lambda x: "NEGATIVE" if x < 0 else "")
    print(dpnl.to_string(index=False))
    print(f"\nPositive days: {pos_days} / {len(day_pnl)}  |  Negative days: {neg_days} / {len(day_pnl)}")

    return smry


def main():
    print("Loading atm_joined_2026.parquet ...")
    df = load_data()
    dates_count = df["date"].nunique()
    print(f"  {len(df):,} rows | {dates_count} days | "
          f"{df['timestamp'].min().date()} to {df['timestamp'].max().date()}")
    print()

    trades_df = run_backtest(df)

    if trades_df.empty:
        print("No trades generated.")
        return

    out_trades  = OUT_DIR / "v47_trades.csv"
    out_summary = OUT_DIR / "v47_summary.csv"
    trades_df.to_csv(out_trades, index=False)

    smry = print_summary(trades_df, dates_count)
    if smry is not None:
        smry.to_csv(out_summary, index=False)

    print("\n" + "=" * 72)
    print("ROBUSTNESS -- Jan-Mar (train) vs April (test)")
    print("=" * 72)
    t = trades_df.copy(); t["date"] = pd.to_datetime(t["date"])
    for label, sub in [("Jan-Mar (train)", t[t["date"] < "2026-04-01"]),
                       ("April   (test) ", t[t["date"] >= "2026-04-01"])]:
        if len(sub) == 0:
            continue
        w  = (sub["pnl_per_lot"] > 0).mean() * 100
        gp = sub[sub.pnl_per_lot > 0]["pnl_per_lot"].sum()
        gl = abs(sub[sub.pnl_per_lot <= 0]["pnl_per_lot"].sum())
        pf = gp / gl if gl else float("inf")
        slh = (sub["exit_reason"] == "SL_HIT").sum()
        avg_dur = sub["duration_min"].mean()
        print(f"  {label}  n={len(sub):>3}  win={w:>5.1f}%  "
              f"net=INR {sub['pnl_per_lot'].sum():>9,.0f}  PF={pf:>5.2f}  "
              f"SL={slh}  avg_dur={avg_dur:.1f}min")

    print(f"\nSaved: {out_trades}")
    print(f"Saved: {out_summary}")


if __name__ == "__main__":
    main()
